function gcd(a, b) {
    return b === 0 ? a : gcd(b, a % b);
}

function findGCD(nums) {
    const minVal = Math.min(...nums);
    const maxVal = Math.max(...nums);
    return gcd(minVal, maxVal);
}
```

    The algorithm implementation follows these steps:

1. Define the gcd() function, which will compute the greatest common divisor using the Euclidean algorithm.
2. Create the findGCD() function, which takes an array of integers (nums) as an argument.
3. In the findGCD() function, find the minimum and maximum values in the given array. This is done using various min/max methods depending on the language used: std::min_element/std::max_element (C++), Arrays.stream (Java), min/max (Python), or. Math.min/Math.max (JavaScript).
4. Return the gcd of the minimum and maximum values found in step 3 by calling the gcd() function.

This finds the greatest common divisor of the smallest and largest numbers in the given array.

